    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Mean absolute relative error of 8.3% in NIH prediction is within the 15% acceptance criterion. Grid convergence is confirmed with GCI below 3%. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40-2018 assessment matrix. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is satisfied across all evaluated operating conditions. The assessment team accepts the model for the stated context of use.",
